						<div class="postbody">It's not the best list, but it's still useful. I think there's a ton of stuff from 1988 that meets the question you asked, though? Even if you have to weed out some that you consider &quot;false positive&quot;.<br /><br />You can also see a dramatic drop-off by 1990. I don't think that's merely the selection bias of it being a poor list.<br /><br />(I wonder if the <a href="https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E3%83%87%E3%82%A3%E3%82%B9%E3%82%AF%E3%82%B7%E3%82%B9%E3%83%86%E3%83%A0%E3%81%AE%E3%82%B2%E3%83%BC%E3%83%A0%E3%82%BF%E3%82%A4%E3%83%88%E3%83%AB%E4%B8%80%E8%A6%A7" class="postlink">corresponding Japanese article</a> is better maintained?)</div>

